September 24, 2025... I'm here to check if this song actually reached 6 Billion. I was so surprised. I was here when this music video was first released. Like I watched this vid 20 mintues after it was initially posted publicly. The views were like around 20-30k. I was 17 years old at the time and I thought this song flopped. I remember liking it, but I just thought it flopped at the time. I do hear this occassionally being played on events and radio stations but I didn't think much of it over the years. 8 years later, I scrolled to a youtube shorts to find out that this song got 6 Billion views. I was shocked. I don't know, I find this boring story cool enough to share. It's nothing really important, it's not life changing. But the fact that I thought Shape of You flopped for 8 years straight is just bewildering to me, to say the least.

The sun is a part of the universe and provides vitamin d for humans. The sun is much bigger than the earth. Also the sun provides energy for plants. The sun doesn't judge anyone, it just shows up in the sky. Also without even seeing the sun I know it's real because I can feel the heat on a hot day. The sun is very powerful. So how do we pray to the universe? The universe responds to how you feel. It's really important that you feel good. The universe responds to this vibration. - Focus on what you are greatful for, including the little things. - Visualize what you want and feel yourself having it. - Think about what you want. - Write down and read about things you want. - Trust your instincts (instincts are ususally right most of the time). Trust your instincts as long as you don't hurt anyone else. - Ask the universe for what you want - Do things that make you feel great about yourself. - Do things that make you feel happy. - Make a vision board with pictures on it of things you want. - If you aren't sure what you want I recommend visualising Gold, gold is valuable. - You could also visualise golden light healing your body or something else you want (light giving you adrenaline for example) You could also visualise white light healing your body, white represents purity. - If you aren't sure what you want pray for the FEELINGS and EMOTIONS you want. - If you aren't sure what you want pray for oppotunities for the feelings and emotions you want. For example if your bored with life start praying for oppotunities to find healthy ideas for excitement. Start exploring different options and hopefully you find an exciting activity. If your angry in life work on your attitude and pray for oppotunities to find the calmness your need. Don't get desperate when praying. Pray, have faith in the universe and yourself. Yes put the work in when required, this is very important aswell. Try one or all of these ideas above and see how much better your life will become. If you have a different idea that works then great, keep using that. In times of stress do healthy and appropriate things to take your mind off the situation and improve your mood. You could write down things you want and visualise them. Now sometimes you will feel negative during your life and this is ok. Sometimes a little negative energy or stress in the body is good to keep you motivated. Sometimes negativity and stress can be great as a warning sign, example drinking too much alcohol and having a hangover. This feeling tells the body to slow down on the alcohol. When exercising your body is put under stress but there are many health benefits associated with exercise. Now if you feel negative and stressed for too long this is not good for the body. The body and mind struggles to deal with too much negativity and stress. Trust me I know. Great examples are holding onto anger for too long about a certain issue. Also abusing drugs and alcohol puts the body and brain under lots of stress. Now when under stress I recommend trying to get happy again. Easier said than done, I know. The universe responds to how you feel and positive thoughts are much more POWERFUL than negative thoughts. For example if you are feeling bad about people suffering when watching the news, maybe don't watch the news anymore or could you work out a solution to help. If you can't do nothing to help maybe you could pray for them to get better. It's ok to show emotions, it's just what we do with the emotions and how we react to these emotions that determines our quality of life in my opinion. Agradecimentos especiais a: The Hintertux Glacier, Áustria; Hohenhaus Tenne e Hotel Neuhintertux. Sobre Ed Sheeran: Ed Sheeran pode ser o astro pop por excelência da década de 2010: um cantor e compositor internacionalmente aclamado e multipremiado que parece não reconhecer fronteiras entre estilos ou eras, com elementos de folk, hip-hop, pop, dance, soul e rock presentes em sua música. Seu incrível catálogo inclui os álbuns de estúdio "+" (mais), "x" (multiplicar) e "÷" (dividir), que geraram singles de sucesso como "The A team", "Lego House", "Sing", "Thinking Out Loud", "Photograph", "Shape Of You", "Castle on The Hill" e "Perfect". Em 2019, Ed Sheeran lançou o abrangente 'No.6 Collaborations Project', que contou com uma ampla gama de artistas, incluindo 'Justin Bieber', 'Camilla' Cabello', 'Travis Scott', 'Eminem', 'Cardi B', 'Paulo Londra', 'Bruno Mars' e 'Stormzy', entre muitos outros, produzindo sucessos como 'I Don't Care', 'Beautiful People', 'South of The Border' e 'Take Me Back To London'.

I honestly really hate how the promo/singles of Play are being handled. I get releasing a song or two as singles in the months leading up to an album's official release. That makes sense. But this whole concept of literally releasing half the album before the official release date just does not sit well with me and it honestly has kind of put a damper on my excitement for Play. I actually really enjoy the experience of binging an album's track list once it comes out. And it's nice to know one or two of those songs ahead of time. It's such a special moment to press play on a tracklist of 12+ tracks and experience the whole thing new at one time. (I mean Subtract in numerical order is essentially a whole narrative of Ed and his family's journey through that tough stretch and wouldn't nearly have been as inpactful or meaningful if half the songs had randomly been released beforehand!). But with Play we already now have essentially half the album (and most likely the half that is expected to be most popular. Think A side tracks vs B side tracks theory). 
I think this kind of release schedule honestly kind of hurts Ed and the album in the long run (and maybe even loop tour). Sure he can bank all of the streaming numbers and money from merch drops now before the album has even officially come out, but what's this going to mean when Play finally releases? The market (fans, streaming) have now been so oversaturated in Play promo, singles, and merch for months that by the time the rest of the album drops next month, is "anyone even going to care"? (To put it bluntly). 
And in some ways I could even see the argument being made against Ed saying that this type of singles releasing makes him look desperate and even is a bit of a money grab. 
This is just my own unpopular opinion. But I really hope that by the time we're coming up on the next album that Ed and his team have had a good think on the subject and do not follow this same pattern again.

My first unpopular opinion is that many in this sub dislike the fan obsession with the charts but in reality its the result of a fan base cultivated by Ed himself being obsessed with the charts. Even though he claims he isnt now, there was a time he embraced chart topping, as said by the song Tides from Equals.

The other unpopular opinion I have is that Ed actually never did try to replicate the success of Divide. He had yet to make an album that is full of what couldve been singles. Divide was an album full of songs Ed claimed couldve been a single. None of his *solo* albums since have been that. People claim Equals but thats just not true when you have songs like Sandman on it.
Perfect is overplayed =-

The success of Shape of you was the undoing of Eds ability to write unique lyrics and the beginning of The Brand. 

Firstly, Ive been a die-hard since about 2010. All the EPs, all the albums, and I love him. This is the man who got me into songwriting, so credit where credits due. 

I remember being completely infatuated by his early lyrics- especially from SIWWA right up until the deluxe versions of X. There was a rawness to his storytelling- you could really feel the emotion in his vocals. The production wasnt too overwhelming and managed to just amplify these amazing amazing songs so much so that they are still perfect to listen to. 

Then Divide drops, the world goes crazy and he becomes this almost ubiquitous figure- and not just in music. Hes everywhere. SOY plays about 100 times on any radio station and he becomes inescapable. That marimba line is one of the most recognisable melodies in modern pop and I love it at the same time as I hate it, because lyrically, its a weak song. 
Granted, it got people up and dancing, and the Fresh Meat reference was an ode to Britishness, but for me it just lacked everything I fell in love with. 
Perfect was always going to be a hit, but even that didnt feel like it had half the soul of Wake me up, photograph or Afire Love. It had no vulnerability. 

No6 had some great collabs but there was nearly a video every other week, and I feel like people were kind of like thanks for the songs for the summer and it was relegated to the shelf. 

Then = is announced and I have hope. Hope which is snatched as soon as I hear Shivers. A great bop, but the lyrics felt so bland it was like pop-music-korma. Overpass Graffiti is brilliant but it should have had the same type of production quality as Nina because the triple guitar tracking was too much, but the lyrics felt personal- finally! 

- was an absolute belter, and one of my favourite releases to date. The lyrics were poignant, heartfelt and you could really finally feel the man behind the music again. However, I still think for an acoustic album, the production quality was over the top. He should have recorded that album with Jake Gosling, as he did with +, not Aaron Dessner. Almost like the studio said this is great, but we still need it to be semi-commercial 

Autumn Variations gets an honourable mention, and Plastic Bag should have done something commercially- the only song with great lyrics which could have fared well had it had the overproduction of all the other singles. 

Right now, Azizam and sapphire have been okay to listen to when they appear on shuffle, but I am LIVING for A little more. It feels authentic. It doesnt meet the universal convention of a good pop song, but IT IS! Its tongue in cheek, its funny, the lyrics are honest- its great to hear Ed Rap again and its a breath of fresh air. Its been on repeat constantly. 

I sound like Ive come to shit on an entire decades worth of work, but thats not the case at all. I love Ed, I just believe that Shape of You has had him shackled for 8 years in the pop machine, and hes finally starting to break free, which is liberating as a listener.
Ed and Beyoncé are two of the best artists weve had over the past decade. I dont think any new male artists even come close to touching Ed
